OL,3,CAsda fined for selling out of date
OL,4,Cfood at two Welsh stores
OL,6,FKerry Nicol, external affairs manager
OL,7,Fat the Chartered Trading Standards
OL,8,FInstitute, said: "Supermarkets have a
OL,9,Flegal and moral responsibility to
OL,10,Fensure that food on their shelves is
OL,11,Fsafe and within its use by date.
OL,13,F"Selling food past its use by date not
OL,14,Fonly breaches consumer protection laws
OL,15,Fbut also risks public health and
OL,16,Fundermines trust.
OL,18,F"Trading Standards teams across the
OL,19,Fcountry play a vital role in
OL,20,Fmonitoring compliance and taking
OL,21,Faction where necessary.
